The club’s fortunes have ebbed more than they have flowed over the years, their survival anchored in that idealism of being the “people’s club.”And unlike other outfits that have come and gone, Muthaiga RFC, Ruiru, Machakos SC, Thika SC, Kenya Breweries RFC, Barclays Bank RFC, Stanchart Bank RFC, Faru RFC, Ulinzi RFC etc, Mwamba --43 years old and counting, will stay and find a new home. It was heartening news to the passionate rugby fraternity in the country when the union recently released tentative Kenya Cup fixtures for the 2021 season.
After more than a year of inactivity due to the Covid-19 pandemic elite rugby will be returning to the Kenyan pitches.
Mwamba RFC will play their first game at home to Blak Blad on February 27. This season will be the first since 1978 that the proud and resilient Mwamba will not have Nairobi Railway Club as their designated home ground.



